Nakita namin yung libro mo, yung itim na ink ang gamit tapos parang manipis yung sulat. Di rin the best ung penmanship pero naiintindihan pa naman.

Tinago po namin ung libro mo sa ceiling tiles. Bakit? Kasi sadista po kami. May isang ceiling tile na nagagalaw, inangat namin tapos pinatong sa katabing tile.

Happy hunting po ng libro ;)

My opinions after the 1st month of being a CCJE Lasallian:

Pros:
-Super welcoming at friendly ung Student Gov! May libreng snacks nung first week ginawa ko tuloy caf√® bar kasi maraming klaseng kape dun haha
- Super friendly rin block ko! Kinabahan ako sa una kasi I came from a private school na 22 kami pero doble population namin sa block, butiSee more nlng medj open sila sa isa't isa at nagkaroon agad ako ng circle of close friends haha
-Maganda ung outdoors ng UD! Ito tlga ung place na tipong lalakarin ko tlga na may peace of mind haha kasi medjo camp ung feel nya at parang therapeutic sya sakin

Cons:
- There are some facilities na pinapasukan ko na parang need iayos, may isang room na parang butas ung binatana tapos there was one time na basa ung floor kasi sa ulan
- Some orgs are medj pushy magrecruit? Idk kung pano ko sya iexplain kasi baka lang to sa pagiging introvert ko, pero parang instead of being intruiged or interested sa org nila nappressure ako kaya as much as possible binibilisan ko nlng lakad ko thru JFH tents para di nila ako mapansin
- Nakakastress inavigate ung SB, especially pag nakamobile lang ako huhu kasi nakatago tlga ung to do list sa website kaya kailangan ko tlgang hanapin un pag maglolog in dun

Might notice more after ng September pero tignan nlng po natin haha

Not that I am assuming to be greater than the varsity members currently chosen, but my online rating on chess.com is around 2000+ for all the major time formats (blitz, rapid, and bullet), and on lichess, I am 2100 in blitz and 2200 in rapid.

For my FIDE rating, I am only rated at around 1500 for rapid since I only participated in a FIDE rated tournament once this year, which was my first and only time of participation in an official chess tournament as of the moment, but that doesn't mean that my playing strength is only at the level of 1500. (For those who do not know what these numbers meant, in chess we have an Elo rating system to measure someone's playing strength).

As a matter of fact, I have defeated several chess masters online, which are internationally recognized by the governing body of chess (FIDE) ranging from candidate masters to FIDE masters, and even international masters in puzzle battle.

Pls, if any chess varsities are seeing this post, kindly comment so I can message you about how to pursue my dream of becoming a patriot. My PE teacher said that If I think I have the potential, then I may ask those people who have knowledge regarding this matter.

Also, if you want to play a game of chess, me and my friends are frequently in the library during our free time to play some blitz chess. We are also planning to create a chess club if many people in the university are interested in chess. :)

Regarding sa nagpost about PE swimming, based on my experience, sadly opo ganyan talaga yung ibang prof.

As someone na hindi marunong lumangoy, trauma lang din inabot ko sa swimming class na yan.

Yung prof nga namin (lalaki), di ko nakitang bumaba sa pool habang nagtuturo.

Andon lang siya sa taas nagmamandate on what to do.

Worst experience nung palunod na ako, nakita niya ako pero di manlang hinagisan ng floater.

That swimming class was never beginner friendly at all.

Gets ko naman na yung point ng swimming class is for us to learn how to swim, pero dapat iconsider din na hindi lahat marunong.

Kung di nagcancel ng classes dati dahil sa pandemic, baka umabot na ako sa ospital.

I am not generalizing every prof sa swimming class, kasi may mga nakikita ako before na tinuturuan talaga yung mga beginners.

Nakikita ko andoon din sa pool kasama students while teaching and kudos to these kinds of prof!!

To OP, I suggest try to ask if pwede magpalipat ng prof, or magpa alternative PE (i heard may ganito raw) and I hope ma-grant ka, good luck!!

Stop caging your child/children in your watch.

Please don't disagree too much if gusto nilang mag extra curricular activities like orgs.

They are losing opportunities...BIG opportunities na sakanila na mismo lumalapit.

Just because you're worried about them doesn't mean naSee more kailangan niyo po silang i-tago sa mga bulsa niyo.

Them joining orgs are actually them enjoying their teenage and students years kase most of them is not allowed or is afraid to ask for your permission pag niyayaya sila ng friends nila na "gumala" lang sandali after class.

Please, that's normal and alam po namin na naranasan niyo din po yan.

Babad na babad po sa acads ang students ngayon and ung pag sali sa extra curricular activities are just a (mostly) coping mechanism lang nila yun to enjoy themselves.

It‚Äôs been almost a month and wala pa din kaming teacher sa isang subject namin.

Puro sub lang lagi and we‚Äôre really LEFT behind.

Meron pa kaming final output for finals na collaborative activity for all major subjects pero ni isang idea for that class wala pa din.

We had a substitute teacher last meeting and super fit niya para mag teach saminSee more but unfortunately, for sub nalang siya kasi ayaw niya daw magturo kasi stressful(ikaw nalang po pls huhuhu).

Sabi nila is yung prof talaga namin doon ay Manager (?) ng isang agency and walang free time to teach.

Then why hire someone who does not have the time to teach?

Students ba ang mag aadjust kung biglang i fe-feed kami ng sobrang daming informations in a short period of time when hindi naman namin kasalanan na wala kaming prof?

Buti sana kung hindi kami nag babayad ng tamang amount sa tuition eh! If you‚Äôll think about it pa, one week nalang midterms na and we don‚Äôt have any idea pa kung ano ba talaga i e-exam namin???

Other sections must be laughing at us na kasi we‚Äôre so clueless to everything about that subject. Yung naturo palang samin is dapat pang beginning of class lang! Kamusta naman binabayad namin?

We even had classes sa lobby kasi wala na available room na pwedeng gamitin (centennial is ginagamit ng ibang class and yung fr rooms naman is isa gamit din ng ibang section tas yung isa pinipinturahan pa).

I find it so disturbing na tipong wala na nga kaming building, wala pa kaming teacher. Isa pa yung sa tour na next month na yung tour pero wala pa din nilalabas na statement if magkano ba yung estimated amount. Idea man lang if how much babayaran.

Dati sabi boracay for about 30k pero baka madagdagan pa? 30k?!?!
Sobrang bigat ng tour na to with almost a month to prepare na maglabas lang ng pera.

Not everyone has the capacity to release an amount with a short period of time lalo na at ang mamahal ng tickets niyan for sure kasi malapit na at ni isang release ng uniform updates wala pa din.

Kahit nga pag kuha lang ng uniform sizes eh at nakakahiya sa ibang schools na kapag nakita kami is iba iba design and color hue ng business attires namin.

Kahit nga neck ties and scarfs man lang wala kaming pare parehas.

Kahit bumawi nalang sana sa nameplate pero wala pa din.

Matatapos na siguro kaming mag aral dito sa La Salle pero hindi pa din namin mararanasan maka experience mag suot ng business attire na uniform talaga ng La Salle.

Yung pare-parehas lahat sa department.

Please sa Department namin, do better. Kung nahihirapan kayo, mas nahihirapan students niyo.

If sasabihin niyo na puro reklamo naman ang alam, then I‚Äôll tell you what.

We have every reason to complain kasi hindi namin nakukuha yung deserve namin sa tuition na binabayaran namin each year.

Almost 150k++ per year with low quality facilities, uniforms, and education? I don‚Äôt think so.

yung mga comments tulad ng "magresign na si x" "ambulok ng x" "walang kwenta naman tong x" "tangina ni x" with no further explanation as to what part makes them feel that way or what points for improvement can they consider ay yung tinutukoy kong hindi na counted as constructive criticism. applicable pa ba ang "mapuna lang mali akala inaatake na pagkatao mo kahit na hindi naman talaga"?

Hello, alam ko madaming nadisappoint about sa rescheduling ng cscs olympics.

Ito lang po masasabi ko as athlete.

Yes, exctied tayo kasi makakalaro na, pero ang iniisip napo kasi ng ibang participants is yung self satisfaction lang nila, di niyo napo naiisip yung Goals ng CSCSSG para sa CSCS Olympics.

Para saken ang understanding ko sa goals nila is maging successful na madaming participants pero less gastos, kaya hindi na nila nirequire na dapat may jersey bawat team, kasi sa tagal ko nang athlete nag cocompete kami na color coding lang, di naman need na may number and may name sa likod.

Di ako member ng sg pero na inis ako sa sinabi nung isang participant sa meeting, ang SG po natin ay walang malaking budget na kagaya ng CBAASG na kayang mag organize ng malalaking events.

Ang gusto ng sg natin is mag introduce ng new sports na hindi pa kilala sa bansa natin, ang gusto nila is maexperience ng ordinary students yung saya habang naglalaro ng sports.

Yes andun yung dapat competitive pero let's give way naman po sa students na gusto lang maglaro.

Athlete din ako pero gusto ko din maglaro, pero if need ko ibigay ang slot ko para sa student na gusto maglaro, i will give my slot to them kasi chance nila yon para maexperience yung sport.

About naman sa preparations, I know kung gaano kahirap mag pa sched ng facilities, lalo na ngayon na hindi pwede maglarovsa ULS gamit na gamit ang MTH Court.

Nakakasabay ko din kasi sa RCC yung members ng CSCSSG na nagpapasched, papirma dito, papirma doon, minsan pag balik mo wala yung need mag pirma kaya need mo pa bumalik kinabukasan, then pag punta mo kinabukasan may mga need kapang gawin bago nila pirmahan, to the point na may nauna nang organization na nagbook nung sched na dapat para sa CSCS Olympics, naging short ang preparations dahil yung mga mas matagal na nadates is nakuha na ng ibang orgs or sg kaya kinuha nila yung natira at available na slots.

Then isa pa, 1st meeting palang sinabi na nila na ang mga program councils na ang magiging incharge if want magpagawa ng mga teams nila ng jersey.

Personally thankful ako na namoved ang schedule kasi hindi talaga ready, yung mga beginners na nakapasok sa first come first serve bigla bigla nalang sila lalaban?

Syempre super risky nun hindi nila alam yung injuries na pwede nila makuha if bigla nalang sila lalaban.

Well i'm sure hindi naman lahat ng members ng team na nabuo nyo is beginner, meron naman na jan na sumasali sa mga liga ng volleyball and basketball.

Can't we just support and appreciate their efforts at kung kayo busy sa kanya kanyang school works, sila din busy and mas madami silang paper works pag dating sa office ng SG.

Trust me ngayon merong confusions and nakaka disappoint talaga pero at magiging successful to pag nag start na ang events.

Let's focus muna sa pag submit ng requirements, kasi isa sa reason kung bakit namove ang olympics is dahil sa incomplete na medical certificates.

Athletes tayo, pinakamagandang attitude ng isang athlete ay ang pagiging patient.

Sana wag na natin masyadong sisihin ang CSCSSG and ang mga PC kasi I'm lahat yan sila nahihirapan as of now, hindi rin makakatulong if puro reklamo ang mababasa nila.

That's all thank you ü´°

This is for all the students out there. Please read.

As part of the student government before, I can say that being in it really is an eye-opener.

Maiintindihan mo bakit some plans can't push through and why some plans are delayed.

It isn't because of the student gov all the time.

It is most of the time sa admins.

Tandaan, ang officers ay sumusunod lang sa patakaran ng nasa itaas at wala din silang magagawa tungkol sa sistema.

May mga times na akala mo good to go na ang event pero hindi pala kasi may kulang na papel, may hindi sang-ayon sa mga admin, at marami pang iba.

Mahirap din magplano ng event kasi ang daming kailangan pirmahan, ipasa, sulatan, magcompute magkano ang costs ng electricity, venue, housekeeping, at iba pa.

Sadly, kung hindi ka student government or wala kang kaibigan na student government, hindi ka maeexpose sa realidad kung gaano talaga kahirap maging isang lider.

Ako, isa ako sa mga naiinis din kapag namomove ang event, kapag nacacancel, at iba pa.

Pero nung pumasok ako sa student government, naiintindihan ko na kung gaano siya kahirap, kung gaano nakakainis minsan na ang admin ang cause ng delay, kung gaano kahirap maglatag ng plano na ang dami mong iisipin kagaya ng kung kaya ba ng budget at iba pa.

Now, the reason I'm posting this is because of the posts I see regarding a CSG because of their intrams. I am not saying na they aren't lacking at any part. I don't know them personally but all I can say is, I know how hard it must be for them na macancel ang event nila. And even if may lapses on their part, let us give them some slack kasi hindi nila kasalanan lahat.

Let us cut our sg's some slack guys. Tao din sila. Estudyante din sila. Hindi madali maging lider at maging estudyante. Hindi din madali na patuloy na intindihin ang mga nakakataas. Huwag tayong magalit at manira dahil lang da isang event. Isang event lang yan at hindi dahil diyan ay mahuhusgahan niyo na kung gaano kabuti ang isang CSG. Tandaan, event lang yan.

Lastly, lahat tayo ay biktima ng sistema na magulo. Matagal na itong problema ng mga CSG dahil kami mismo ang nakakaranas nito directly kahit dati kaya pilit nating intindihin ang ating mga CSG dahil ginagawa lang din nila ang makakaya nila para sainyo at sa department niyo.

Hiii, may tots lang ako regarding don sa CSCS Olympics.

1. It is commendable that CSCSSG had the accountability regarding their mistakes and lapses.
2. Sobrang gulo ng announcements and registration for the event.
3. Obvious ang miscommunication between CSCSSG and the PCs since nagulat ang exec ng PC namin nung sinabing sila raw ang magcocompile ngSee more list of interested players for the event.

What could have been improved?
1. Interest check - this may be irrelevant for most students pero required ito ng admin before makapag-organize ng event. Mas advisable na naka Google Forms din ang interest check dahil kawawa ang block rep namin habulin para pasagutin ang mga blockmates naming di pumapasok kaya ang ending is di nakumpleto and late yung block namin sa interest check.
2. Player registration - it is also advisable na una pa lang, sinabi na clearly na individual ang registration sa forms. Ito rin dapat yung point na "first come first served." Di pa dapat hinihingi ang team gallery and med certs at this point dahil first come first served ang policy and possible na may players na kumuha ng med cert pero di makakapaglaro dahil may ibang nauna sa kanila. Iiinput ni interested student sa GForms yung information na required sa player gallery (name, age, CYS, FB profile, 2x2 pic, etc.). Speaking as a former district level competitor, nauuna talagang icompile ang list ng players BAGO asikasuhin ang team gallery and med certs.
3. Release of team roster - pagkatapos ng registration is dapat idisclose agad kung sino yung nakapasok sa teams based sa first come first served policy. Then pwede sila icontact gamit yung FB profile na nilagay nila sa player registration to confirm their slots.
4. Team gallery and med cert - after the players confirmed their slot, saka na iaccomplish ang team gallery and med certs para maiwasan ang unnecessary workload sa SG na iniisa isa yung documents na pinasa ng students dahil sa GForms nila pinasa and who knows how much responses the GForms got. This is also to avoid confusion on the possible redundant documents na naenter ng teams dahil nga individual registration daw so kung 12 ang players, malamang may 12 na same team gallery and compiled med cert ang napasa. It is unnecessary time lost sa end ng SG.

Random things I also observed.
1. Chess doubles??? - never akong nakakita ng chess doubles in my life of representing my former school sa district sports competitions. Though unsure ako kung ganito pa rin ang ruling considering the multiple changes in the guidelines.
2. Scrabble doubles but yung isang player is nakatingin sa dictionary and the other places the letters sa board??? - ito ay same energy ng pangongodigo sa exam. In scrabble, ang scorer lang ang pwede tumingin sa dictionary kapag may nangyaring "challenge" sa isang specific word na nilapag ng opponent. Both players ang naglalagay ng letters sa board pag doubles and i-aadd ang score per pair at the end of the game.
3. Di naannounce sa original meeting with the presis na may athletics din na kasama.

Disclaimer: Take this with a grain of salt dahil di natin alam fully ang happenings behind the scenes.

For everyone na may concern sa DL at Latin.

1. For DL - no lower grade than 2.50 in all subjects and must attain 3 or above sa average.
3.00 - 3.50 - second honor
3.51 - 4.00 - first honor
(Kung 1.75 nakuha mo sa midterms tapos nakakuha ka ng 3.25 sa finals magiging 2.50 ang total nun, goods pa din yun)
Computation kasi is midterms + finals √∑ 2 so wag na malito bumawi ka lang.

2. Pwede ka maging DL kahit nung first sem laglag ka kasi every sem naman ang pagiging DL pero ibang usapan ang Latin Honors. Pwede ka ding maging DL kahit nagshift ka basta yung grade ok.

3. Latin Honors - No grade lower than 2.50 in all subjects and average must be
3.26 - 3.50 cumlaude
3.51 - 3.75 Magna
3.76 - 4.00 Summa
Kumbaga average toh ng lahat ng average mo mula 1st year to 4th. So if sa isang sem may 2.25 ka sa isang subject kahit na mag DL ka next sem mawawala ka na sa Latin. (In short, DL ka dapat every sem to be qualified sa Latin).
*pero in case lang na di ka nag DL sa isang sem pero wala kang lower than 2.50 kunwari average mo 2.98 e 3 need for DL, basta walang lower than 2.50 and basta sa end ng 4 years ay ma attain mo yung average for latin pwede pa din naman. Gets ba? Sana nasagot na lahat ng tanong nyo üòá

Hello. I'm just here to ask for advice or suggestion, I'm an opinionated person lalo na when it comes to social issues whether it's local or international.

Like some of my friends said I'm too political for my own good though I understand their point of view, politics is exhausting but the thing is,everything is political, the way I see it.

AlsoSee more way back during election season, I also cut my ties with people lalo na relatives ko during election season.

For me kasi I tend to distance my self kapag the people I'm talking to has different core values than me. Like I had a friend who I had to cut off due to his homophobic tendencies knowing most of our friends are part of the LGBTQ community.

Not to mention, I'm also a humanities student and I'm planning to take a major related to the that field.

So one of my friend groups told me that I should calm down with politics and tone down my shared posts about politics.

For context, I'm a bit of a progressive person, still I'm flawed and have a lot to learn.

Though I'm a bit wary of apolitical people which is something I need to work on I guess.

So here's the thing, should I tone down my political side and compromise with my friends who aren't that involved in politics or should I distance myself from them?

I care about them but my values and their values are different and not going to lie, it's one of my dealbreakers in a relationship.

I don't want to be called bigot tho.

P.S. One of my friends tend to read a lot of posts from these FW so I'm hoping they wouldn't recognize me.

Sa SWAFO na po binigay ang trabaho na manghuli ng students na lumalabag sa handbook rules to prevent the scenarios na awayin ang mga guards ng students/parents even though ginagawa lang nila trabaho nila.

About sa dress code, you can access student handbook of the univ online or try looking at the old post of your college dep kasi afaik, nag post sila ng dress codes nung pwede nang mag onsite classes.

posting my two cents kasi ang oa ng mga tao masyado when it comes to relationships.

1. hindi totoo ang three month rule.
‚Äî una sa lahat, iba-iba tayo ng relasyon. hindi tayo pare-parehas ng pinagdadaanan sa isang relasyon at walang makakaalam ng totoong totoo kung hindi yung dalawang magkarelasyon lang. aanuhin mo ang "three month rule" kung puno ng micro cheating yung relasyon nyo? wala rin. hindi mo masasabing walang respeto ang isang tao sa ex nya dahil lang may bago na sya in less than three months dahil as people, iba-iba tayo ng pacing sa pagmomove on. hindi porket umabot kayo ng ilang taon ay dapat ilang taon na rin ang pagmomove on ng isang tao. pano kapag nagmomove on na habang nasa relasyon kasi toxic pala yung ex? walang rights ang ibang tao magsabi na "may bago na sya, nag cheat siguro to habang sila pa tapos nakipagbreak lang para di matawag na cheater". ayusin nyo mindset nyo on things minsan.

2. relationship is nothing but a trend nowadays.
‚Äî bakit ba uhaw na uhaw kayo sa relationship? nothing's wrong with having some color sa love life nyo pero wag naman sana na pati sa simpleng fling lang, or simpleng landian lang, tingin nyo magjowa na agad kayo. flings or "landian" are short lived. hindi yan matagalan and mabilis talaga kayo mapapalitan. wag na wag kayong magcommit sa taong hindi nyo kayang pag-committan. at mas lalong don't blame someone if they can't commit at all, lalo if kinlaro naman sa inyong di sila willing or ready magcommit. sana rin magheal muna kayo to an extent na stable na kayo bago pa kayo mag enter sa isang relationship dahil it requires patience, understanding and gentleness. tigilan nyo kakalovebomb at "fast kasi pacing ko in relationships" nyo, inooverwhelm nyo lang partner nyo. stop projecting your traumas and negative emotions, and becoming unavailable din kapag hindi kayo ok dahil hindi naman dump site ang partner nyo for you to do so. partner yan hindi therapist kaya wag ka nang bumoses at ijustify yang reasons mo.

3. remain solid on your ground
‚Äî respect your partner at wag ka basta basta magpapadala sa mga sinasabi or experiences ng friends mo. iba sila, iba kayong dalawa. not everything that applies to them will apply to the both of you. stop telling the entirety of your relationship to everyone that you know dahil nakakadisrespect din yan sa partner. it's also the root cause of misunderstandings, peer pressure and it could also be someone's manipulation tactic against you kung kwento ka nang kwento tungkol sa love life mo. keep everything private, there's always an evil eye amongst the crowd waiting for you and/or your partner's downfall.

i have a lot to say pa pero that's going to be it for now. let's all be mindful when we enter in relationships and when chasing someone.

27 The Chase

[Woody looks between Buzz and the van then made a decision. He jumped down and ran back to Buzz. The van begins pulling out of the driveway. Woody tugs on a loosened slat and breaks Buzz free of the fence. The two toys ran out to the street but the van is already driving away down the street]
[Then they heard a rumble and they look back to see the moving truck rolling towards them]
Sheriff Woody, and Buzz Lightyear: Aaaah!
[They duck down to avoid been hit by the truck as it rolls over them. After it passes, they start to chase it]

[Scud is lying on the front porch when he perks up, seeing Woody, and Buzz running down the street after the moving truck. He growls, wanting to get back at them for duping him. Buzz runs faster than Woody and leap for a strap which is dangling from the back of the truck and grabs it to climb up to the bumper. Woody struggles to reach the strap but it keeps being out of reach]
Buzz Lightyear: You can do it, Woody!
[Woody jumps and grabs the strap]
Woody: Whew, I made it! (laughs)
Buzz Lightyear: (gasps)
[Woody look back to see Scud running towards them]
Woody: Aaaaaah!
[Scud bite on Woody's foot]
Woody: (kicking Scud with his other foot) Get away, you stupid dog! Down! Down!
[Scud began to drag Woody down to the end of the strap]
Buzz Lightyear: Hold on, Woody!
Woody: I can't do it! Take care of Andy for me!
Buzz Lightyear: No!
[Buzz jumps off of the truck and onto Scud's snout. He pull Scud's eyelids and snap them hard. Scud yelps in pain, letting go of Woody. He bucks wildly with Buzz still on him]
Woody: Buzz!
[Still hanging onto the strap, Woody scrambles up onto the bumper. He unlocks the back door of the truck and strains to get it open. Just then, the moving truck and the family van stop at the traffic lights. Woody slams into the door, making it slide up, carrying him with it. Hanging from the door, Woody scans the inside of the truck until he saw a box marked ANDY'S TOYS. Scud flings Buzz off his face. Buzz tumbles under a parked car. Scud runs to the car but can't get to Buzz due to the car too big for him to fit under. Woody open the box and inside is Slinky, Rex, Mr. Potato Head and Hamm]
Toys: What?
Rex: Are we there already? Woody!
Slinky: Woody?! How'd you -\-\
Hamm: How did you -\-\
[Woody push the box to the side and begin rummaging through the next box. Slinky, Potato Head, Rex and the other toys poke their heads out]
Hamm: What's going on? What's he taking?
Woody: Ah-hah! There you are!!
[The toys watch in confusion as Woody took out RC and his remote control out of the box]
Mr. Potato Head: Hey! What's he doing?
[Woody runs to the back of the truck and kicks RC out onto the street, making the toys scream in horror]
Rex: He's at it again!
[Woody turn on the remote and send RC to the parked car, pasting Scud on the way. RC's motor whirrs happily at Buzz being OK and Buzz smiles at him]
Woody: (laughs)
[The traffic light turned green, allowing the moving truck and Andy's family van to drive on]
Mr. Potato Head: Get him!
[The toys pour out of their boxes and charge towards Woody]
[Woody look back, gasps and quickly turn the wheel on the remote, making RC zoom with Buzz on board him towards the truck with Scud in hot pursuit. Woody steers the remote while trying to fend off the angry toys]
Woody: Ah-h!! Ah-h! No, no!
[Scud continues chasing Buzz and RC down the street, nearly close to chomp on him. In the truck, Rocky lifts Woody and spin him around in circles]
Woody: No, no, no! Wait!
(as Rocky spins him)
Woody: Whoa-Whoa-Whoa...!
[RC suddenly starts going around in circles because of the remote going around in Woody's hand]
Buzz Lightyear: (spinning) Whoa-Whoa-Whoa...!
[Rocky throws Woody to the floor, making RC going straight again with Scud still chasing him and Buzz clinging to him. Hamm leaps off a pile of boxes and onto Woody]
Hamm: Pig pile!!
[The impact makes RC jumps into the air and back onto the road. Buzz lands on RC, facing backwards. The traffic lights turn red and the wall of cross traffic move from both directions. Buzz looks back to see the lines of traffic in front of him]
Buzz Lightyear: Aaaah!
[He and RC drives straight into the lines of traffic with Scud blindly following them. Scud saw a car slamming on it's brakes on his side and went wide-eyed, realizing his mistake and skids to stop. The car swerves to avoid Scud and crashes into another car. Buzz and RC zipped through before the other cars collide with each other. Soon there is a multi-car pile up that encircles Scud, trapping him. He runs back and forth, trying to find a way out while people in their cars honk their horns at each other and shouting at each other]
Woman: Get out of that car!
Man: Move it!
[Buzz look up to see the crash and let out a sigh of relief, both for getting away from Scud and avoid getting hit by the cars. Back on the truck, Rocky holding Woody (still holding the remote) above his head and walk towards the open door]
Woody: No! Wait! You Don‚Äôt Understand! Buzz is out there! We've gotta help him!!
[He swung his arm and the remote around, accidentally knocks Mr. Potato Head's hat, eyes, mouth and nose off his body and onto the floor]
Mr. Potato Head: Toss him overboard!
Woody: No, no, no, wait! Ah!
[The toys throw Woody out into the road. The toys cheered as the truck rolled away]
Rex: Hooray!
Mr. Potato Head: So long Woody!
[Woody sighs in relief as he looks back and sees a blue car coming towards him. He ducks down to avoid getting hit as the car passes over him. Shaken, Woody gets up when Buzz and RC come racing up behind them]
Buzz Lightyear: Who-o-o-oa! Woody!
[RC sweeps up Woody and keep driving. Woody found themselves sitting in front of Buzz while still holding the remote]
Woody: Well, thanks for the ride.
Buzz Lightyear: (pointing ahead) Look out!!
[They see that they're about to slam into the rear tire of the car in front of them. Woody screams and quickly turns the wheel on the remote to make a hard left, missing the tire. RC swerves under the car]
Woody: Now let's catch up to that truck!
[He flick the switch from ON to TURBO and RC speeds up towards the moving truck.
[The toys are busy congratulating one another when Lenny glances out of the back and spots Woody, and Buzz]
Lenny: Guys! Guys! Woody riding RC! And Buzz is with them!
Toys: What?!!!
[The toys rush to the edge of the open truck. Bo lifts Lenny up to look through him]
Bo Peep: It is Buzz! Woody was telling the truth!
[The toys including Mr. Potato Head gasp in shock and horrified at what they have done]
Slinky: What have we done?!
Rex: Great. Now I have guilt.
Woody: We're almost there.
[RC is gaining on the moving truck]
Bo Peep: Rocky, the ramp!
[Rocky rush over to a lever on the side of the back. The sign above it reads "RAMP: UP/DOWN." Rocky push down the lever and the ramp starts to lower down. Woody, and Buzz look up to see the ramp about to come down on top of them]
Buzz Lightyear: Look out!!
[RC sped back just before the ramp slams down into the road. Sparks flew from the metal, scraping the road]
Slinky: (to other toys) Quick! Hold on to my tail!
[Mr. Potato Head and Rex grab on to Slinky's tail, allowing Slinky's front end to jump off the truck and onto the ramp. Slinky lean forward with his paw stretch out to Woody. Woody hands the remote to Buzz and leans forward to grab Slinky's paw. They grab hold of each other]
Mr. Potato Head: That a boy, Slink!!
[Then all of a sudden, RC starts to slow down, pulling Slinky's front end off the ramp]
Slinky: Woody!!
[His slinky middle began to stretch and the other toys look worried]
Slinky: Woody! Speed up!
Woody: (to Buzz) Speed up!
Buzz Lightyear: The batteries! They're running out!
[RC's headlight eyes sag as he slows down even more. As Slinky continues to stretching, RC began to weave side-to-side like a water skier]
Slinky: Whoa! Whoa! Whoa!
[Inside the family van, Molly look at the sideview mirror and saw RC with Woody, Buzz in it before they back out of view. Molly squeals with delight by the sight of what she saw. With Slinky's mid-section stretched to the limit, he began to lose his grip on Woody]
Slinky: I can't hold on much longer!
Woody: Slink! Hang on!
[Slinky's paws slips out of Woody's hands, sending his front shooting back into the truck and knocking over the toys]
Slinky: Aaaaaaah!
Toys: Ouch!
[RC slows down and sputters to a stop. Woody and Buzz watch in vain as the family van and moving truck disappear down the street. A cuckoo bird's chirps]
28 Rocket Power
Woody: (disappointed) Great!
[Buzz drops the remote in disappointment as he looks back at the rocket, which is still attached to his back which gives him an idea!]
Buzz Lightyear: Woody! The rocket!
Woody: The match!
[He pull out the match from his holster that Sid had put there earlier]
Woody: Yes! Thank you, Sid!
[Wood runs around behind Buzz, strikes the match against RC's back tire and is about to light the fuse when a car whizzes over them, blowing out the match. Woody looks stunned at this, clenched the match in his hands and falls prostrate to the ground]
Woody: No-o-o! No-no-no-no! No-o-o!
[Unable to watch a cowboy cry, Buzz bows his head, causing his helmet to block the sun from Woody. As Buzz's shadow moves over him, Woody stop sobbing and suddenly saw a white dot on his hand which is the same dot generated from Sid's magnifying glass. Seeing that Buzz's helmet aims the sunlight on his hand, Woody got an idea. He leaps up, grab Buzz's helmet and aligns it so the sunlight touches the fuse]
Buzz Lightyear: Woody?! What are you doing?
Woody: Hold still, Buzz!
[The fuse lights]

Slinky: I shoulda held on longer.
[Lenny look out of the back and saw Woody, Buzz, and RC zooming up to them]
Lenny: Look! Look! It's Woody and Buzz! Comin' up fast!

[The rocket is so strong that it began to lift Woody and Buzz into the air. Woody manages to hold on to RC but not for long as he forces to lose his grip, sending RC towards the moving van]

ULS has a great view in my opinion, you can view people by the greens and yet you are covered by them, watching them in plain sight. only few people go there most of the time because its a sports complex at bihira lang ang p.e students from time to time. its nice and quiet and if may swimming lessons sa olympic pool, you can hear the splash of water and the whistle which is nostalgic enough.

the only downside is the way up there is too steep, and will take you a few minutes and an empty lungs to get there.

coffee is good and cheap whether its hot or iced coffee. i only recommend their hotdog sandwiches (cheap too) since i'm not a fan of junk foods.

may tatlong community cats doon(?-isa lang ata), the water fountain serves very cold water (yun lang may malamig na water sa buong lasalle, kaso krazy ang agos nya), and you can doze off under the sun since ang laki ng shade ng puno doon. another downside is malanggam yung mga outdoor na stone tables haha + daming nagpbabagsakang bulaklak.

i have stayed and read my book there and the sun is so warm kahit tanghaling tapat idk why. that's all xoxo.

Just had a rough time with GenMath today. But something happened that time that really made me think. It was a classmate of mine who, the same as my situation, was having a bad time like me. The difference however was he had a bunch of friends that were there to comfort him and make him feel like he's not alone in the struggle. God I wish I had friends/someone like that dito sa UD, to feel like you "belong" but I can't. Even though I am "a part" of a friend group, they don't bring me the comfort and company I expected. They do the opposite, cracking jokes sometimes about me which aren't funny but instead are annoying and make me angry (one joke almost made me want to punch that smug face they had, thinking they were a comedian) but most of the time they ignore me. I always have to constantly put up a mask to make them pay attention to me at least once but I can feel it shrink, deteriorate, and one day fall off. I desire something, someone, somewhere, a state of not existing but still conscious; a free soul that can roam around this beautiful world of ours but not face its harsh realities, explore the beauty humanity has to offer but at the same time not participate in its chaotic cycle. I desire the unattainable, I'm just a comedian telling myself this joke over and over again. Once I laughed at this joke of mine but not anymore, I still find it funny, but this deep abyss I have made for myself is overwhelming. Maybe one day that big event will come at my life, to finally roam around freely in this world without a care in the world and be who I want to be. Though they will still ignore me (to whom can a ghost even talk to?), but at least I can finally sit down and contemplate the beauty of life in a peculiar way.

P.S. Picture comes from a 1997 movie called The Taste of Cherry by Abbas Kiarostami.

mapapa-"everybody's falling in love and i'm falling behind" na ako.

to be honest, hearing my circle of friends talking about their other halfs, including them in their trips, plans, and random topics related to their partners makes me feel so left out in those topics, giving me the sense of urgency to have a special someone as well.

but at the same time, i still don't want to commit or at least have the decency to find somebody to love. some friends tend to tease me with other people or our classmates, which i don't like; or telling me to install dating apps, which is really not my thing to do. maybe it did work out to some of my friends, but it feels like it's me having the 'desperate' move to have a relationship with someone.

i mean, i just recently moved on from someone whom i used to loved (we never even got together at all), who has a new relationship with someone. i'm happy for them though! when i actually found out about it to someone, since we don't talk even if we're blockmates, i never felt any ache in my heart unlike before, as long as they're happy. going back, i just feel like not having someone at the moment. i honestly don't know if it's a bad decision but i do feel left out sometimes with these 'relationship' topic since most of them have their partners already.

Hello, pa-rant lang po ng todo.

May groupwork po kami na need ng filming, well yun yung napagusapan namin, sila rin yung nag-suggest, September 20 pa namin yun napag-usapan. Same groupings din sa project namin sa mismong Subject nayon.

Ngayong araw yung deadline, and ako yung pumili bilang editor, walang leader sa group namin pero lagi akong nagi-initiate kung ano-ano mga gagawin like ako gumawa ng format ng script sa acting, ako gumawa nglyrics, ako yung laging nagtatanong sa kanila kung pwede na ba nila gawin yung gento-ganyan, pero never akong namilit, ang line ko is '' Hello makakaya po ba ng by this time/day?'' ang never silang nagr-respond ng maayos, ang most respond lang ay heart react or ''sige gagawin ko mamaya, sorry busy rn'' which is gets ko kasi same lang naman kami ng mga gawain kaya alam ko gaano kami katambak, which is why hindi ko sili pinipilit agad gumawa.

Pero ito po ha, ilalagay ko na dito mga date na nag-update ako sa kanila kung ano-ano gagawin and mga tanong ko kung pwede na ba nila magawa, kas shems grabe kung masasabihan akong baka salita lang ako.

September 20:
Nag request ako na mag-start na gumawa ng script para sa project and para sa lyrics sa docs after classes sa following day.

September 21:
Nag-aya ako na sabay-sabay gagawa para updated lahat. Natuloy? Hindi, busy daw. Naka-ready na nun yung lyrics para madaliaan sila sa pagpapalit. Hinahandle ko rin yung main project namin that time so todo update ako.

September 23:
Isang member lang may gawa and 3 sentences something lang yon, pero nag-update ako sa gc na nagcomment ako sa docs keme keme and sinabihan yung mga groupmates na matatalino kung paano uli sila makkatulong para lowkey to let them know to start working na.
Sinabi ko narin na need dapat namin magshoot that week, para hin matambakan. PARA HINDI MATAMBAKAN ok?

September 25:
Nanghihiram ako ng camera para makapagvideo ng fillers in case makulangan sa scenes, walang nagdala the next day.

September 26:
Sinabihan ko yung 2 speakers sa group namin na pakituloy na ang paggawa, kasi wala nang nagdagdag after days. Pero hindi ako nagset ng time kung kelan nila needd tapusin kasi alam ko talaga kung paano kami katambak, kaya onting action lang thankful nako, pero after that ay heart react lang and wala paring progress sa docs. Nakakaiyak yung araw araw mong tinitignan kung ilan viewers sa docs in hope na maramdaman kong atleast binuksan nila.

September 27: nag-ask ng suggestion, and sinabihan silang nagv-video narin ako dito sa bahay ni hopes na mamotivate sila. Nagpilit narin akong pumili sino kakanta kasi isa lang nagvlunteer. Thankfully that night 4 na ang singers, which is kasama ako, eh ayoko in the 1st place kasi piyukin ako.

October 1:
Ayun na, nagset nako ng deadline kasi wala parin pala silang ginawa ng ilang araw. Pero atleast ayun nagstart na yung isa gumawa, ang ganda nya kamo gumawa and siya yung tahimik sa class pero napaka cooperative if nakausap mo ng maayos.
Naginform ako ng hapon na may prac sa gmeet at 8:30, and wow ha, napaka cooperative nila, I mean sila yung matatalino na laging on time nagpapasa so yeah, pero diko na-expect kasi nga ghoster sila sa gc. Thannkul ako that night and mas maganda suggestion nila kesa sa mga naisip kong lyrics.

Btw, may different meeting din kami nun ng 8:00 kasi officers kami, nag-start ako maglay pu ng plano namin sa teachers day.

October 2:
Nagpameeting uli ako para sa practice, yung matatalino biglang last minute nagpasali sa pagkanta, pero sinabi nila yun after ng practice naming mga singer kaya di sila nagprac and i dont mnd kasi mas alam nila yung song so I assumed na alam na nila pano kantahin.

Dapat Monday na recording namin kesa ngayong friday na nga yung deadline, pero tambakan daw so na move ng wednesday.

Wednesday nagfilm na, aba grabe pasaway sila tawa ng tawa eh hindi nga kayang magubos ng time kasi need ng ibang members sumama sa ibang groups sa ibang subject.

Takte ayoko na pala mag-explain ng mga nangyare. All I want to say is editor lang kinuha kong role, it was my own decision to help in every single thing so I would appreciate ny effort. Pero bakit ang nakuha kong response ay ''Hello dapat proper communication kung wala pa palang nagagawa keme'' eh 11 sya ng gabi nagchat kagabi. Eh ang sirap magedit ng mga boses, ang panget actually ng gawa ko, pero yun na yng best na makukuha namin, inedit ko yung speed ng boses para makasabay sila sa chorus, need ko i-adjus yung background noise, need ko magmessage ng 1 am kagabe kasi yung sinend nila sa gmail ay hindi mabuksan.

Nab-bitter lang ako sa pag call out nya sa gc na bakit di ako makipagcommunicate sa mga ginagawa. How dare you seek proper communation po when all the days I ask for your presence never kayong nagr-respond ng maayos. Bakit kung kelan deadline na tsaka lang kayo aging active ang makaasta kayo na kayo yung may malaking ambag kasi sunos sunos na mga suggestion nyo, KUNG KELAN MALAPIT NA DEADLINE. Kaninang hapon sila nagtulungan sa paggawa and hindi ako nakatulong pero feel ko yung intention nilang iparating na sila lang yun nagng ''active'' and '' may ambag'' eh ang dami kong ginawa behind the scene para sa kanila. Well i wont really care about that if hindi naganap yung pag call out, kasi nakakhiya yun.

Ako na yung editor para sa music video pero bigla agad kayong nagdecide na wag na kasi kulang sa scnens, edi parang natanggalan talaga ako ng role, na pabigat at late maggawa ng recording ng boses.

Hindi sila matatawag na pabigat kasi ang laki rin ng contribution. Hindi ko na alam san napunta ang sinabi ko, pero torn ako between never na uling maginitiate sa groupings kung ganyan ang kalalabasan or dapat magpatuloy lang kasi as a president need ko maging responsible and to lead. Sorry po sa long rant.

Shoutout naman ho diyan kay Sir Gumiran, na I believe handles major and minor subjects related sa humanities. I was his student sa Contemporary World last sem. All na I can say ay his lectures, at first glance are organized chaos.

Tapos sa bandang dulo na it all makes a lot of sense. He often shares insights and viewpoints na laging related to whatever topic under the sun. Whether you agree or disagree sa kanya, lagi kayong may new info na malalaman, mapa modules, assessments o sa meetings. Minsan nga lang overflow of information, but I appreciate it. Nambabasag siya ng mga pananaw, tapos ginaguide rin kayo para magkaroon ng sarili ninyong punto. He says na he is a nationalist and a pragmatist: kanyang pake lang is if ideas can be applied to reality, and if it can strengthen the country. As per him, walang karapatan mag reklamo ang Pilipinas from those ideas, dahil kung ang Vietnam ay napag iiwanan na tayo in some aspects, ano pa ang maipagmamaybang natin. Nasa 20s din ho ata si sir, kaya nagulat kami first meeting na siya yung mag hahandle ng aming sem.

Saka pala sort of running gag niya is to always remind us, na most problems natin ngayon, ay laging may connection to the American and the British Empires. Di ko rin makimutan na he began our discussion of the contemporary world, way back to the Mongol conquests. Out of the box lagi. Maswerte ang mga dadaan sa kanya, yan lang masasabi ko.
Ang coping mechanism po natin ay ang magpost sa FW

I'm speaking from what I know and what I've observed. So it may not be the case for others.

It is just frustrating that what we are doing right now that we thought was just for the sake of our own turns out to be an event of this group of people as well. Something academic is at stake so we (the students) are doing our best to have theSee more best outcome, but it turns out it is not just for our academic purpose but surprisingly an organizational event. At first, I thought that there was nothing to worry about until we asked to pay for that event. Why do I need to pay for my entrance and/or expenses for that event if we the students are also organizing that event for our own academic purposes? We are already spending on our own outputs, and now they also expect us to pay for their organizational event or agenda? I mean why do we need to pay the tokens for judges, our OWN medals and certificates (if we won that event), the organization members‚Äô ID & meals, judges' meals, the tents (diba indoor yung sa 2nd year?), even the performers??? I will forget about the cost of the event‚Äôs decorations I guess if it is for the overall visuals‚Ä¶ But is it really needed for that organization to handle this or make this event? Can‚Äôt it just be a final output for our grades? We build our own output, we present it, perform what is needed, and then the professors will judge us. I don‚Äôt know why it should be like this. Yes, you provided transparency and I am surprised about the expenses. I do also hope that all the expenses are being budgeted wisely (yung tipong naghanap talaga ng murang supplies) and I hope kaya pang bawasan yan at makapag recycle kung kaya pa.

It may just small amount for you guys or you may be thinking na ‚Äúnag aaral ka at need talagang gumastos‚Äù pero di lahat kayang ibigay agad agad yun. Porket lozol kayang bayaran lahat? Duh? It's disheartening to witness how students treat, react to, and perceive organizations :(

This just highlights how underappreciated organizations are.

It's crucial to recognize that members of organizations are also students, managing the balancing act of academics and organizational responsibilities to serve the student body and enhance YOURSee more university experience.

They strive to provide the best despite facing challenges such as limited funds, manpower, and the ongoing patience required in coordinating with university offices.

Seeing my student leader friends wake up early and sleep late to fulfill their org responsibilities while excelling in academics and yet being unappreciated by fellow students is heartbreaking.

I understand that joining an organization was their choice and something they willingly embraced, but I hope that, if not appreciation, at least respect can be extended to them.

Please be a bit kinder to them.

If you have any problems or concerns, remember that organizations exist to LISTEN TO STUDENTS.

You can always reach out to them.

Contrary to the belief that they operate effortlessly, EVERY ACTION HAS A PROCESS THEY HAVE TO FOLLOW.

They must adhere to the university‚Äôs rules and guidelines.

Even before the school year begins, they need to plan and submit events for the semester, undergo signatures, approvals, edits, and endless revisions of numerous papers.

Some organizations are even responsible for handling the final output of certain subjects, as required by their departments.

Despite their efforts, they receive minimal benefits, such as recognition, certificates, or medals, with no tuition fee discounts, and often, no funding at all for their organization.

If only you could experience what they're going through, hindi kayo magrereklamo nang magrereklamo ng ganyan :)

As part of an org for sure you voluntarily join and are ready to take on any tasks and responsibilities.

Joining it you know for sure that you need to put so much effort and put aside your academic loads.

With that in mind, if you want to organize an event for your org you should not just be ready physically but also financially.
Moreover, you may be doing events for your fellow students but you should at least consider that if your fellow students are willing to join especially if there is something to pay for.

Maybe some don‚Äôt want to join an org or be an active participant in your event because they don‚Äôt want any more responsibility and can‚Äôt afford or budget to do so.

I know that there is a membership fee to be able to join your org but I don‚Äôt question that because I know di naman ako sasali kaya sino naman ako para pakialaman pa yun pero now naiinvolve kami so I just want to speak up.

We can‚Äôt discredit you for being an active org and putting so much effort into your own event since it is your passion for sure, but I guess we can‚Äôt just push or expect every student to be an active participant and contribute to your organization tasks, especially if there is money contribution.

We don‚Äôt join any org because we can‚Äôt anymore, physically and financially. Thank you for your endless hard work but if you organize an event you should be ready na mapagod at gumastos, and not expect anything from anyone.
